Aardvark combine (#7)

* Adding optional combine flag to API

* Forcing an error if combine is used with a smaller count than the number of results to avoid unexpected results.

* Changing the way the API handles bool type arguments.

* Enabling totalAuthenticatedEntities combine to be a sum of all roles using that service.

* Returning error code 400 if combine is set but count is less than total items.

* Fixing Flasgger/swagger syntax from bool to boolean.

just check if 'all' is in the list.

Fix Aardvark Update (#51)

This commit fixes a bug introduced by the previous change to
move to the Access Advisor API. Specifically we needed to convert
the new AWS API datetime to epoch, but the object was never added.

This caused updates to not happen.

Revert to milli epoch (#53)

This commit puts Aardvark back to milli epoch. Previous changes
moved to seconds epoch, but the logic that checks whether we're
doing an update looks to see that the new time is greater than
the old time. So everybody that upgrades won't get updates unless
we match the old format.
